00:49:53.000 --> 00:49:55.090
Next is Twitter.

00:49:55.460 --> 00:50:03.130
Now as I'm sure everyone's familiar,
Twitter is an incredibly popular service.

00:50:03.210 --> 00:50:06.220
People send more than a
billion tweets per week.

00:50:06.440 --> 00:50:09.720
And we hear from a lot of our
customers on iPhone and iPad and

00:50:09.810 --> 00:50:12.120
iPod Touch that they love Twitter.

00:50:12.180 --> 00:50:16.120
And so we want to make it even
easier for all of our customers

00:50:16.120 --> 00:50:18.290
to use Twitter on iOS products.

00:50:18.290 --> 00:50:20.380
We're doing a number of things for this.

00:50:20.810 --> 00:50:22.690
First, we're adding single sign on.

00:50:23.000 --> 00:50:27.860
So now, when you go to the settings app,
it's built in on the iPhone or iPad.

00:50:27.960 --> 00:50:33.110
You can enter your username and password
and now you're configured for Twitter.

00:50:33.220 --> 00:50:35.220
For any app you download
off the App Store,

00:50:35.350 --> 00:50:37.310
it'll just say can
I use your credentials?

00:50:37.360 --> 00:50:39.180
When you say yes, you're logged in.

00:50:39.180 --> 00:50:41.550
You don't need to re-log
in every single time.

00:50:41.590 --> 00:50:43.440
So single sign on.

00:50:47.520 --> 00:50:51.270
Next, we've integrated Twitter in
with many of our apps,

00:50:51.460 --> 00:50:53.400
like camera and photos.

00:50:53.400 --> 00:50:55.850
So now if you're at a concert
and you take a photo and you

00:50:55.920 --> 00:50:59.400
want to tweet that photo,
just tap on the action button,

00:50:59.430 --> 00:51:01.730
it's a new option tweet,
and it brings up this

00:51:01.730 --> 00:51:03.780
beautiful tweet sheet.

00:51:05.610 --> 00:51:08.140
It gives you a nice
thumbnail of the photo,

00:51:08.170 --> 00:51:11.700
gives you a countdown of how many
characters you have left to type,

00:51:11.700 --> 00:51:15.490
and you can even optionally
add your location,

00:51:15.490 --> 00:51:17.500
tap on that,
and then you've tweeted the photo.

00:51:17.500 --> 00:51:19.890
It's that simple.

00:51:25.210 --> 00:51:29.220
In addition to tweeting
from photos and camera,

00:51:29.260 --> 00:51:32.940
you can tweet articles from safari,
websites.

00:51:32.940 --> 00:51:35.890
You can tweet videos from YouTube,
and you can tweet about

00:51:35.960 --> 00:51:38.740
businesses or locations from maps.

00:51:38.740 --> 00:51:42.700
Beyond all of this,
we added integration with contacts.

00:51:42.750 --> 00:51:45.490
Now you might have a lot of
contacts that don't have photos,

00:51:45.700 --> 00:51:48.420
but Twitter may have
photos for those people.

00:51:48.420 --> 00:51:52.500
And so you can use Twitter to
automatically update the photos

00:51:52.610 --> 00:51:58.000
in your contact list and even
the @ username for your friends.

00:51:58.150 --> 00:51:59.940
And that's Twitter integration
throughout the OS.

