01:19:18.210 --> 01:19:21.100
So I get to talk about iCloud.

01:19:21.100 --> 01:19:25.280
We've been working on this for some time
now and we're really excited about it.

01:19:25.600 --> 01:19:30.940
About 10 years ago,
we had one of our most important

01:19:30.940 --> 01:19:36.420
insights and that was that
the PC was going to become the

01:19:36.480 --> 01:19:39.950
digital hub for your digital life.

01:19:41.340 --> 01:19:42.180
What did that mean?

01:19:42.180 --> 01:19:46.080
Well, it meant that that's where you were
going to put your digital photos.

01:19:46.080 --> 01:19:48.110
Where else were you going to put them?

01:19:48.710 --> 01:19:54.230
Your digital video off your digital
camcorder and of course your music.

01:19:54.230 --> 01:19:54.940
Right?

01:19:55.040 --> 01:20:00.320
You were going to acquire it in the
device or potentially on your Mac.

01:20:00.320 --> 01:20:04.890
And you were going to basically
sync it to the Mac and everything

01:20:04.890 --> 01:20:07.030
was going to work fine.

01:20:07.030 --> 01:20:10.630
And it did for the
better part of 10 years.

01:20:10.690 --> 01:20:14.390
But it's broken down
in the last few years.

01:20:14.570 --> 01:20:16.090
Why?

01:20:16.200 --> 01:20:19.500
Well, because devices have changed.

01:20:19.500 --> 01:20:21.490
They now all have music.

01:20:21.970 --> 01:20:24.460
They now all have photos.

01:20:24.460 --> 01:20:25.640
They now all have video.

01:20:25.640 --> 01:20:30.670
And so if I acquire a song,
I buy it right on my iPhone,

01:20:30.670 --> 01:20:34.480
I want to get that to my other devices.

01:20:34.500 --> 01:20:35.110
Right?

01:20:35.140 --> 01:20:38.500
I pick up my iPad and it
doesn't have that song on it.

01:20:38.590 --> 01:20:41.500
So I have to sync my iPhone to my Mac.

01:20:41.730 --> 01:20:44.500
Then I have to sync my other
devices to the Mac to get that song.

01:20:44.500 --> 01:20:47.510
But then they've deposited
some photos on the Mac,

01:20:47.510 --> 01:20:51.500
so I have to sync the iPhone again
with the Mac to get those photos.

01:20:51.500 --> 01:20:56.410
And keeping these devices
in sync is driving us crazy.

01:21:03.000 --> 01:21:03.990
and many more.

01:21:04.000 --> 01:21:06.160
We have a great solution
for this problem.

01:21:06.160 --> 01:21:09.460
And we think this solution
is our next big insight,

01:21:09.460 --> 01:21:15.800
which is we're going to demote the
PC and the Mac to just be a device.

01:21:15.840 --> 01:21:20.200
Just like an iPhone,
an iPad or an iPod touch.

01:21:20.200 --> 01:21:24.630
And we're going to move the digital hub,
the center of your digital life,

01:21:24.920 --> 01:21:27.160
into the cloud.

01:21:27.160 --> 01:21:30.480
Because all these new devices have
communications built into them,

01:21:30.820 --> 01:21:35.140
they can all talk to the
cloud whenever they want.

01:21:35.140 --> 01:21:37.170
And so now.

01:21:37.610 --> 01:21:41.710
If I get something on my iPhone,
it's sent up to the cloud immediately.

01:21:41.710 --> 01:21:44.020
Let's say I take some pictures with it.

01:21:44.080 --> 01:21:48.530
Those pictures are in the cloud
and they are now pushed down to my

01:21:48.530 --> 01:21:51.700
devices completely automatically.

01:21:52.470 --> 01:21:57.130
and now everything's in sync with me
not even having to think about it.

01:21:57.130 --> 01:22:00.630
I don't even have to take
the devices out of my pocket.

01:22:00.630 --> 01:22:03.300
I don't have to be near my Mac or PC.

01:22:04.710 --> 01:22:10.260
Now some people think the cloud
is just a hard disk in the sky,

01:22:10.310 --> 01:22:10.500
right?

01:22:10.680 --> 01:22:15.950
And you take a bunch of stuff and
you put it in your Dropbox or your

01:22:15.950 --> 01:22:19.440
iDisk or whatever and it transfers
it up to the cloud and stores it

01:22:19.480 --> 01:22:22.640
and then you drag whatever you want
back out on your other devices.

01:22:22.640 --> 01:22:27.260
We think it's way more than
that and we call it iCloud.

01:22:27.260 --> 01:22:32.210
Now iCloud stores your content
in the cloud and wirelessly

01:22:32.530 --> 01:22:34.930
pushes it to all your devices.

01:22:34.930 --> 01:22:40.790
So it automatically uploads it,
stores it and automatically pushes

01:22:40.980 --> 01:22:43.530
it to all your other devices.

01:22:43.700 --> 01:22:48.500
But also it's completely
integrated with your apps and so

01:22:48.500 --> 01:22:51.860
everything happens automatically.

01:22:51.860 --> 01:22:52.150
And so you can see that
iCloud stores your content in

01:22:52.150 --> 01:22:52.620
the cloud and automatically
stores it to all your devices.

01:22:52.620 --> 01:22:55.920
And there's nothing new to learn.

01:22:57.340 --> 01:23:00.200
It just all works.

01:23:00.200 --> 01:23:03.020
It just works.

