Now, the three core apps in
MobileMe were Contacts,

01:23:33.060 --> 01:23:34.700
Calendar, and Mail.

01:23:35.000 --> 01:23:38.270
Three things we'd obviously
like kept up to date.

01:23:38.270 --> 01:23:42.780
We've thrown them away,
we've re-architected and rewritten them

01:23:42.780 --> 01:23:46.930
from the ground up to be iCloud apps.

01:23:47.160 --> 01:23:50.380
and we've put them on all of our devices.

01:23:50.380 --> 01:23:56.230
So, as an example, in contacts,
when I make a new contact on my iPhone,

01:23:56.230 --> 01:24:00.900
it's automatically brought up to the
cloud where it's stored on the cloud,

01:24:00.900 --> 01:24:05.140
right, the truth is on the cloud,
and then it's automatically

01:24:05.140 --> 01:24:08.950
pushed down to my other
devices so they're all in sync.

01:24:09.050 --> 01:24:10.180
It's that easy.

01:24:10.230 --> 01:24:15.520
I just update a contact on my iPhone
and don't even think about it and that

01:24:15.660 --> 01:24:20.190
contact is updated on all my other
devices and if I change it on any device,

01:24:20.280 --> 01:24:26.260
it's updated on all devices wirelessly,
automatically without me doing a thing.

01:24:27.570 --> 01:24:30.360
So that's contacts, here's calendars.

01:24:30.500 --> 01:24:32.360
Works much the same way.

01:24:32.360 --> 01:24:36.710
I make a new calendar event on my iPhone,
it's stored in the cloud,

01:24:36.940 --> 01:24:39.060
and it's pushed to my other devices.

01:24:41.150 --> 01:24:41.950
Pretty cool.

01:24:42.110 --> 01:24:45.390
We've also added calendar sharing.

01:24:45.390 --> 01:24:50.060
So as an example, if I'm sharing a few
calendars with my wife,

01:24:50.290 --> 01:24:53.250
school and soccer calendars, let's say.

01:24:53.730 --> 01:25:00.600
Right, and I add a new calendar for a
teacher-parent conference on my phone.

01:25:00.620 --> 01:25:04.060
It's again automatically
pushed up to the cloud.

01:25:04.920 --> 01:25:09.290
and automatically push
to my wife's iPhone.

01:25:09.290 --> 01:25:15.830
If she adds an appointment
for a soccer game,

01:25:15.840 --> 01:25:20.320
again, goes up to the cloud
and back to my iPhone.

01:25:20.320 --> 01:25:21.720
It's that simple.

01:25:21.720 --> 01:25:27.540
And so calendars has,
it stores your calendars in the cloud,

01:25:28.120 --> 01:25:33.220
changes on any device or push to all your
devices and we have shared calendars.

01:25:33.220 --> 01:25:35.860
We think you're going to
love the new calendars.

01:25:35.860 --> 01:25:37.020
It just works.

01:25:37.020 --> 01:25:39.840
And then we have mail.

01:25:41.430 --> 01:25:45.410
Mail was in the best shape of all,
but it's even better now.

01:25:45.470 --> 01:25:49.400
We give you a mail account at @me.com.

01:25:49.490 --> 01:25:53.630
Your new messages again are pushed to
all your devices and like we're used to,

01:25:53.630 --> 01:25:58.200
your inbox and folders are all
kept up to date on all devices.

01:25:58.370 --> 01:26:02.990
So that's mail and no ads.

01:26:11.000 --> 01:26:15.630
We build products that we want for
ourselves too and we just don't want ads.

01:26:15.670 --> 01:26:17.710
So we can't get there.

01:26:17.840 --> 01:26:22.970
So these are the three apps that
formed the core of MobileMe.

01:26:22.970 --> 01:26:27.800
We used to sell them for a
subscription price of $99 annually.

01:26:27.960 --> 01:26:32.600
As of today,
this product ceases to exist and those

01:26:32.710 --> 01:26:35.840
three apps are now going to be free.

01:26:48.540 --> 01:26:51.680
But we didn't stop there.

