01:52:29.280 --> 01:52:35.930
One, you can sync your new
devices over Wi-Fi or cable,

01:52:36.050 --> 01:52:38.720
and you only have to sync them once
just to get that music on them,

01:52:38.830 --> 01:52:42.740
and then you can rely on iCloud to
take care of getting all your new

01:52:42.740 --> 01:52:46.110
purchases off iTunes onto that device.

01:52:46.830 --> 01:52:51.330
Or, if it's just a few songs you love,
you don't want to leave behind,

01:52:51.360 --> 01:52:55.400
you can buy those songs
that you'll miss on iTunes.

01:52:56.130 --> 01:53:00.390
We're going to offer a third way,
which is called iTunes Match.

01:53:00.390 --> 01:53:02.840
What is iTunes Match?

01:53:03.000 --> 01:53:09.570
Well, iTunes Match uses the fact
that we've got 18 million songs

01:53:09.570 --> 01:53:13.000
now in the iTunes Music Store.

01:53:13.020 --> 01:53:17.410
And the chances are awfully
good that we've got the songs

01:53:17.430 --> 01:53:20.000
in our store that you've ripped.

01:53:20.000 --> 01:53:24.390
And so we wrote software
to scan those CDs,

01:53:24.510 --> 01:53:30.530
the non-iTunes music,
and match it up with those

01:53:30.530 --> 01:53:32.600
songs we have in the store.

01:53:33.210 --> 01:53:34.100
Right?

01:53:34.100 --> 01:53:39.690
And so we can give that music the same
benefits as music purchased from iTunes.

01:53:39.990 --> 01:53:42.540
and it takes just minutes, not weeks.

01:53:42.610 --> 01:53:46.400
If you have to upload your whole
library into some locker in the sky,

01:53:46.460 --> 01:53:49.050
that literally takes weeks.

01:53:49.320 --> 01:53:53.840
This takes minutes because we're
scanning and matching your library

01:53:53.840 --> 01:53:56.360
so we don't need to upload that.

01:53:56.720 --> 01:53:58.060
That large part of your library.

01:53:58.060 --> 01:54:02.590
And the few songs that remain, well,
we'll upload them.

01:54:02.720 --> 01:54:05.680
But with 18 million songs,
we're most likely to

01:54:05.680 --> 01:54:06.900
have what you've got.

01:54:13.400 --> 01:54:18.400
In addition,
iTunes Match will upgrade those songs

01:54:18.400 --> 01:54:21.910
that match the 256 kilobits AAC.

01:54:29.300 --> 01:54:33.420
and iTunes Match cost just $24.99 a year.

01:54:33.420 --> 01:54:36.140
So if you've got a bunch of music,

01:54:37.600 --> 01:54:40.420
If you've got a bunch of music
that you didn't buy from iTunes,

01:54:40.420 --> 01:54:43.880
you can get all the benefits of the
cloud service and more in terms of

01:54:43.900 --> 01:54:46.720
upgrading your music for $24.99 a year.

01:54:46.720 --> 01:54:49.760
Now, if you look and compare
that to some competitors,

01:54:49.820 --> 01:54:52.090
let's just look at
Apple and Amazon and Google,

01:54:52.300 --> 01:54:53.560
you kind of get surprised.

01:54:53.560 --> 01:54:57.110
Because, again,
the library and the cloud,

01:54:57.110 --> 01:54:58.740
we scan and match.

01:54:58.740 --> 01:55:01.720
The other guys, you've got to upload
your whole music library.

01:55:01.720 --> 01:55:05.110
Again, it's going to take weeks.

01:55:06.990 --> 01:55:10.030
Music apps on your Mac and PC?

01:55:10.190 --> 01:55:12.120
Well, you're stuck with a web
app instead of iTunes.

01:55:15.070 --> 01:55:18.140
Upgrade to 256 kilobits per second.

01:55:18.180 --> 01:55:21.010
The other guys aren't
upgrading you at all.

